<Author>globaltravelkid
<Content>Horrible Tea Gone Awry For my partner's 45th birthday I planned an incredible surprise: booked 2 tickets round trip from NYC to LAX. I arranged w/Ariana G at Hotel Bel Air a private table w/swans and candles and flowers for the special Champagne Tea celebration. We flew 6 hours to LAX, rented the car, drove to the hotel, and then were flying home back to NYC on the redeye. My emails confirmed everything. We arrived 20 mins early to the hotel and were told that we had to wait for tea to begin and our table to be prepared. Okay, so in the interim we asked to see a room as there was plenty of occupanc to do this, yet we were asked to wait 20 mins by the fireplace. We did this and staff forgot about us, so we returned to the tea promptly at the time tea offiially begins. Now we were seated and we waited, and waited, and waited for someone to greet us at the table....an unheard of 15 minutes....on my partner's special birthay! Of cousre I hadn' planned this type of a surprise--to fly my partner across the country to be ignored by this hotel staff. So I picked up the phone, explained the situation to the Penninsula, and while we drove there, they prepared a talbe by the fireplace, arrange a private harpist to do 'happy birthday,' and greeted us champagne. That is service on a moment's notice, and we hadn't even the 4 emails that I DID have w/the hotel bel air. I will continue to give my company's business in Beverly HIlls to the Penninsula and not to this stuffy, tired, snobby, and tired hotel staff of the Hotel Bel Air. They should treat everyone as if everyone chose their hotel out of all of the competition just to fly across the country to arrange a special tea service there! 
